---
description: Local development, human in the loop
alwaysApply: true
metadata:
  environments: local
  human: true
---

Before starting, you must always read the global user rules for
the local environment first, unless it has already been included in your
context by Cursor. Read `~/.cursor/rules/local-env.mdc`. If the file is
missing for some reason, warn the user explicitly. Treat it as part
of the "always included" ruleset.

Project-specific validation gates are described in `./agent.mdc`.
